cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM

This paper deals with the task of connecting language and vision, which is a common theme in computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The proposed algorithm involves filtering text terms based on visual discriminative power, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The applications of the discovered concepts involve image tagging, which is a task in multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.CL, followed by cs.IR, cs.LG, and cs.MM.
